MADRID Spain will warm up for Euro 2020 by playing a friendly against Portugal, the Spanish Football Federation (RFEF) announced on Thursday. Luis Enrique's side will face the reigning European champions at the Wanda Metropolitano in Madrid on June 5. Spain's first match of the tournament will be 10 days later against Sweden, with Poland their other opponent in Group E. They will also face the winner from a play-off. The RFEF have already confirmed friendlies against Germany at home on March 26 and the Netherlands at the Johan Cruyff Arena on March 29.  